climbs.name: Stella
climbs.fa: Randy Garcia, Eric Pospesil, and Andrew Davis

content.description: Climb up the slab through a notch into a small right facing corner. Pull up over the corner and make some technical slab moves out left to a flake. Protect yourself as best as possible and then make some tough moves up and then right to protect-able ground. Follow the featured rock up to easier climbing and to a shared anchor with Casey.
content.location: The first slab you come to after hiking past VJs on the main climbers trail.

content.description: Pull through the head wall on jugs, then climb through the dirty dike making a tough slab move to clip a bolt. After clipping the bolt, run it out to the tree anchor.
content.location: Locate the first slab after hiking past the VJs area on the main climbers trail. It is the short vertical wall up and to the left of this slab.

content.description: Climb up the face towards a bulge between the break in trees. Protect yourself and then step up onto the bulge and move right making some scary slab moves without any hands. Once right climb up to the crack and protect yourself. Then continue to climb up and left on featured rock to the anchors shared with Stella.
content.location: The next obvious climbable rock face feature to the  right of Stella. Behind two odd shaped trees in the middle of the main trail.

content.description: Some very fun, but usually over looked climbs with a mix of vertical and slab single pitch climbing.
